SIMPLE: gnathic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gnathic
<hw>Gnath"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>gna`qos</grk> the jaw.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or
pertaining to the jaw.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Gnathic index</b></col>, <cd>in a skull, the ratio of the
distance from the middle of the nasofrontal suture to the basion (taken
equal to 100), to the distance from the basion to the middle of the
front edge of the upper jaw; -- called also <altname>alveolar
index</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Skulls with the <qex>gnathic index</qex> below 98 are
orthognathous, from 98 to 103 mesognathous, and above 103 are
prognathous.</q> <rj><qau>Flower.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gnathidium</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
